# Verification After Changes

- Only run `pnpm typecheck` / `pnpm lint` after large features or refactors touching many files, or when the user explicitly asks.
- For small and medium fixes, rely on IDE linter feedback (ReadLints) on edited files instead of full project typechecks.
- If changes are scoped to one app, use the app-specific command:
  - Backend: `pnpm --filter @hype-stack/backend typecheck`
  - Frontend: `pnpm --filter @hype-stack/frontend typecheck`
- Fix any errors you introduced before reporting the work as complete.
